modules.description: Provides functions for initializing, enumerating, and communicating with HID devices using Lwt for asynchronous I/O. Operates on device handles, reports, and device information structures. Enables real-time input processing from hardware like game controllers and custom USB devices.

Initializes and deinitializes HID device communication, enumerates devices by vendor and product ID, opens devices by ID or path, and performs non-blocking read/write operations on HID devices. Works with device information records and HID device handles, using bigstrings for data transfer. Used to interact with USB HID devices in asynchronous applications, such as game controllers or custom hardware interfaces.
